            "answer_text": "Given that her father, Lee Eastman probably hated Lennon- for justified reasons- I\u2019m guessing no. Lee Eastman was a well-respected American lawyer, specializing in entertainment law. After she and Paul got together, he made an attempt to get Lee onboard the Apple team (I think as manager, since Epstein was gone). The band already had a LOT of issues, and there was a lack of the unanimity which had always been behind their decisions. The other members supported another candidate, but Eastwood came to London to meet with them. The meeting was a disaster. Lennon, and of course Yoko (who as always sat in to give her opinions) apparently made numerous anti-semitic comments about Eastman (whose real name, coincidentally was Epstein). Needless to say, he didn\u2019t take them well. So I\u2019m guessing that Linda wasn\u2019t a fan of the man who insulted her father for no reason. ",
